h embedded JSON payloads exactly as specified.
Let's test the get endpoint too:
bash# Get a real chat ID from the search results first
curl -s "http://104.191.236.122:40001/mem/search?keyword=test&limit=1&key=public-read-2025" | grep -o '"id":"[^"]*"' | head -1

# Test the get endpoint with a real ID (replace with actual ID from above)
curl -s "http://104.191.236.122:40001/mem/get?id=<ACTUAL-CHAT-ID>&key=public-read-2025" | head -10
Now let's configure nginx to serve these endpoints at https://api.nsgia.com/mem/:
bashsudo nano /etc/nginx/sites-available/api.nsgia.com
Add this location block after the existing API blocks:
nginx    # Memory System HTML endpoints for ChatGPT
    location /mem/ {
        proxy_pass http://<redacted.ip>:40001/mem/;
        proxy_set_header Host $host;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $remote_addr;
        proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto https;
        proxy_buffering off;
        proxy_redirect off;
        
        # Keep HTML content type
        add_header Access-Control-Allow-Origin "*" always;
        add_header Access-Control-Allow-Methods "GET, OPTIONS" always;
        add_header Access-Control-Allow-Headers "Content-Type" always;
    }
Then reload nginx:
bashsudo nginx -t
sudo systemctl reload nginx

# Test the HTTPS endpoints
curl -s "https://api.nsgia.com/mem/search?keyword=test&limit=3&key=public-read-2025" | head -10
Once this works, ChatGPT will be able to access:

https://api.nsgia.com/mem/search?keyword=HISTORIC&limit=5&key=public-read-2025
https://api.nsgia.com/mem/get?id=<chat-id>&key=public-read-2025

And get HTML pages with embedded JSON payloads! ?RetryMHack",
